body:
Given the following code: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=0c66dd8d8bd20ca3f994f331d7b10604

```rust
use std::fmt;

#[derive(Debug)]
pub struct Error<'a>(pub &'a str);

impl fmt::Display for Error<'_> {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "{}", self.0)
    }
}

impl std::error::Error for Error<'_> {}

pub fn func<'a>(_x: &'a str) -> Result<&'a str, Error<'a>> {
    todo!()
}

fn main() -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    let s = "abc".to_string();
    let _ = func(&s)?;
    Ok(())
}
```

The current output is:

```
error[E0597]: `s` does not live long enough
  --> src/main.rs:20:18
   |
20 |     let _ = func(&s)?;
   |             -----^^-
   |             |    |
   |             |    borrowed value does not live long enough
   |             argument requires that `s` is borrowed for `'static`
21 |     Ok(())
22 | }
   | - `s` dropped here while still borrowed
```

<!-- The following is not always necessary. -->
Ideally the output should look like:

```
error[E0597]: `s` does not live long enough
  --> src/main.rs:20:18
   |
20 |     let _ = func(&s)?;
   |             -----^^-
   |             |    |
   |             |    borrowed value does not live long enough
   |             argument requires that `s` is borrowed for `'static`
   |             (some reference to the error type)
21 |     Ok(())
22 | }
   | - `s` dropped here while still borrowed
```

The actual cause of this error is very non-obvious. While this example is contrived, the error is easy to run into when using the `nom` crate. I only solved this after finding someone else with the exact same issue: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/55184864/nom-parser-borrow-checker-issue
